1. $s = (L - 1) - r$

In[11]:
import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image_path = 'src/photo.png' 
image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_gray is None:
    print(f"{image_path}")
else:
    image_negative = cv.bitwise_not(image_gray)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(image_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("  ")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(image_negative, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(r'')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

2. $s = c \cdot \log(1 + r)$

In[2]:
import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image_path = 'src/photo.png' 

image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_gray is None:
    print(f":{image_path}")
else:
    c = 255 / np.log(1 + 255)
    
    log_image = c * np.log1p(image_gray.astype(np.float64))
    
    image_log = np.array(log_image, dtype=np.uint8)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(image_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(image_log, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(r' ')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

3. (-) s = c * r^gamma

In[7]:
import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image_path = 'src/photo.png' 

image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_gray is None:
    print(f" ! {image_path}")
else:
    gamma = 0.01 

    image_norm = image_gray.astype(np.float64) / 255.0
    image_gamma_corrected = np.power(image_norm, gamma)
    image_gamma = np.array(image_gamma_corrected * 255, dtype=np.uint8)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(image_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(image_gamma, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(rf'-')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

4.

T:

$$ s = \begin{cases} r & \text{ } r < T \\ (L - 1) - r & \text{ } r \ge T \end{cases} $$

In[8]:
import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
image_path = 'src/photo.png' 
image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_gray is None:
    print(f":   {image_path}")
else:
    T = 128
    image_solarized = image_gray.copy()
    high_pixels_mask = (image_gray >= T)
    image_solarized[high_pixels_mask] = 255 - image_solarized[high_pixels_mask]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(image_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(image_solarized, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f' (T={T})')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

import cv2 as cv
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

image_path = 'src/photo.png' 
image_gray = cv.imread(image_path, cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

if image_gray is None:
    print(f"{image_path}")
else:
    hist_original = cv.calcHist([image_gray], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])
    image_equalized = cv.equalizeHist(image_gray)
    hist_equalized = cv.calcHist([image_equalized], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))

    #  
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(hist_original, color='black')
    plt.title(' ()')
    plt.xlabel(' (0-255)')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.xlim([0, 256])
    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

    #  
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(hist_equalized, color='blue')
    plt.title(' ( )')
    plt.xlabel(' (0-255)')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.xlim([0, 256])
    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
